==English==

===Pronunciation===
[[w:Received Pronunciation|RP]] in {{IPA|/ˌæntiˈklɒkwaɪz/}}

===Adverb===
'''anticlockwise''' (''British'')
#{{not comparable}} Of movement, in a circular fashion so as to be moving to the left at the top of the circle and to the right at the bottom, in the opposite direction to the way the [[hand]]s of an [[analogue]] clock move.

====Synonyms====
*[[counter-clockwise]] (''US''), [[levorotatory]] (''chemistry''), [[widdershins]] (''particularly on a sundial'')

====Antonyms====
*[[clockwise]]

